  "body": "The [detailed workflow section](https://github.com/theupdateframework/specification/blob/409739f2b8601e28d9330eeabeb454d9ef188e7d/tuf-spec.md#5-detailed-workflows) of the spec should clarify what clients should do after a failed metadata check.  For instance, subsection **1.3 check signatures** requires the client to verify that the metadata is properly signed, but what should happen if the metadata fails the check?  The given metadata should definitely be discarded, but what about the client's current version of metadata?",
